    <note>Liu(2) Yuxi [17574] He received the juren in the same sitting as his younger brother, Tingzhi [17525], and therefore must be the Tinggui, who earned the juren in 1132 (Jiangxi TZ, 21.32b), but who used the mingzi, Yuxi (perhaps his zi). However, there was a Liu(2) Yuxi, Yongfeng county juren listed for 1139 (Jiangxi TZ, 21.31b). Yuxi was born in the same year as Xiang(2) Zimin [714], who became his good friend, and he died the year before his younger brother earned the jinshi in 1145. See documentation for Liu(2) Tingzhi.</note>
